            <title xml:id="name1227-2" xml:lang="fr-x-bhs" source="#bib1227-1">Pēṯyōn</title>
            <title xml:id="name1227-3" xml:lang="fr" source="#bib1227-1">Péthion (texte)</title>
            <title xml:id="name1227-4"
                   xml:lang="en"
                   source="#bib1227-1"
                   syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword #syriaca-anglicized">Pethion (text)</title>
            <note xml:lang="syr"
                  type="incipit"
                  source="#bib1227-1"
                  anchored="true">
               <quote defective="false">ܘܡܢ ܒܬܪ ܕܝܢ ܝܘ̈ܡܬܐ ܩܠܝܠ. ܦ̣ܩܕ ܗܘܐ ܗܘ ܗܢܐ ܡܓܘܫܐ ܪܒܐ̣. ܘܥܒܕ ܟܢܘܫܝܐ ܪܒܐ ܩܕܡܘܗܝ.</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="fr"
                  type="incipit"
                  source="#bib1227-1"
                  anchored="true">
               <quote defective="false">Et quelques jours plus tard, ce grand mage avait donné un ordre et il fit un grand rassemblement devant lui.</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="syr"
                  type="explicit"
                  source="#bib1227-1"
                  anchored="true">
               <quote defective="false">ܗܠܝܢ ܘܕܐܝܟ ܗܠܝܢ ܝܘܬܪ̈ܢܐ ܪܕܘ ܡܢܗ ܕܐܬܠܝܛܐ ܕܩܘܫܬܐ ܘܡܠܦܢܐ ܕܫܪܪܐ ܘܣܗܕܐ ܢܨܝܚܐ ܡܪܝ ܦܬܝܘܢ. ܐܢܐ ܕܝܢ ܚܛܝܐ ܕܐܫܬܘܝܬ ܕܥܘܗܕܢܐ ܕܬܫܥܝܬܗ ܘܕܢܨ̈ܚܢܘܗܝ ܐܪܫܘܡ̣. ܒܨܠܘܬܗ ܘܕܟܠܗܘܢ... ܐܡܝܢ.</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="fr"
                  type="explicit"
                  source="#bib1227-1"
                  anchored="true">
               <quote defective="false">Ces secours et d’autres semblables s’écoulèrent du martyr de la vérité, du docteur de la droiture et vaillant martyr Mâr Péthion. Et moi pécheur, qui ai été jugé digne de retracer le souvenir de son histoire et de ses exploits, à sa prière… Amen.</quote>
            </note>
            <note type="editions" anchored="true">
               <bibl source="#bib1227-1" default="false" status="draft">
                  <author>Corluy, J.</author>
                  <title>Historia Sancti Mar Pethion Martyris Syriace et Latine</title>
                  <citedRange>7 (1888), p. 8-44</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="en" type="MSS" source="#bib1227-1" anchored="true">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">ed: ms Londres, British Library, Add. 12174, f. 383-388v</bibl>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="en" type="MSS" source="#bib1227-1" anchored="true">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">ms Damas, Patriarcat syrien orthodoxe, cod. 12/18 (olim ms Dayr az-Za‘faran, cod. 19), f. 132-135 ?</bibl>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="en" type="MSS" source="#bib1227-1" anchored="true">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">ms olim Mossoul, Patriarcat chaldéen, cod. 89 (Scher) (introuvable)</bibl>
            </note>
